      • getKey

        FileSystemDataFormatter.FileSystemIndexKey getKey(String fileName,
                                                  String typeName,
                                                  String indexName,
                                                  boolean expectsTime)
        When using secondary indexing, this is called for storing the data values.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the file name
        typeName - the DataTypeAdapter type name
        indexName - the name of this index
        expectsTime - whether this index/type anticipates time is encoded in the file name (typically raster data only, and not with the secondary data index) *
        Returns:
        an object containing a file name and the expected contents of the file according to this format

      • format

        FileSystemDataFormatter.FormattedFileInfo format(String typeName,
                                                 String indexName,
                                                 FileSystemDataFormatter.FileSystemIndexKey key,
                                                 GeoWaveValue value)
        This is called for storing values in each GeoWave index. Keep in mind that if the datastore is using secondary indexing, the value provided to this method will be the data ID and not the full data value. The full data value will be provided in the data index.
        Parameters:
        typeName - the DataTypeAdapter type name
        indexName - the name of this index
        key - the key for this row, including various GeoWave elements that are anticipated as components of a key
        value - the value
        Returns:
        an object containing a file name and the expected contents of the file according to this format

      • getDirectoryName

        default String getDirectoryName(String indexName,
                                String typeName)
        Gives the formatter an opportunity to override the default directory for each index/type pair. Each index *must* have a unique directory per type name for the system to function properly. Java NIO is used to resolve this name relative to the filesystem data store base directory, so if proper path separators are used for Java NIO to resolve nested directories, they can be specified as well. GeoWave will ensure directories are created prior to writing data.
        Parameters:
        indexName - the indexName name
        typeName - the type name
        Returns:
        the directory name

      • getPartitionDirectoryName

        default String getPartitionDirectoryName(String indexName,
                                         String typeName,
                                         byte[] partitionKey)
        Gives the formatter an opportunity to override the default directory for each partition (when the index uses partitions). Keep in mind the index directory name is already implicitly in the path.
        Parameters:
        indexName - the indexName name
        typeName - the type name
        partitionKey - the partition key
        Returns:
        the partition's directory name

      • getPartitionKey

        default byte[] getPartitionKey(String indexName,
                               String typeName,
                               String partitionDirectoryName)
        This is the inverse of getPartiionDirectoryName so that partitions can be read from the directory structure
        Parameters:
        indexName - the index name
        typeName - the type name
        partitionDirectoryName - the partition directory name that resolves from this partition key
        Returns:
        the partition key represented by this directory
